verbs.description: beman (third-person singular simple present bemans, present participle bemanning, simple past and past participle bemanned)

entries.meaning: (transitive) To furnish or fill with men; man.
examples: Now do so well as to fare to meet me at thine earliest, and as much bemanned as may be; and let us be both together whatever may happen.
